The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
 Friday, April 30, 2004 NATION BRIEFS
	Lucknow: The Lucknow bench of Allahabad High Court on Thursday granted bail to Amarmani Tripathi, the prime accused in the Madhumita Shukla murder case.Justice N.K. Mehrotra, however, has directed the former minister to make himself available during trial and not to seek any adjournment of the trial on personal ground. 																																												The 24-year-old Madhumita, who reportedly had a relationship with the former minister, was shot dead in her residence in Lucknow on May 9, 2003.
	Mumbai (PTI): A court has absolved South African judge Sirajuddin Mohammed Ibrahim Desai of the charges of raping a woman of his own country at a hotel here during the World Social Forum meet early this year. 
	New Delhi: The Supreme Court has ordered that no action be initiated against Mallika Sarabhai on the human trafficking charge levelled by the Gujarat state prosecution, but the police probe could continue. A bench said the charge appeared to have been levelled because the danseuse had filed a petition in the Gujarat riot cases seeking action against errant officials.																																												 Chennai (PTI): Madras High Court on Thursday held that the POTA Review Committees order to withdraw cases against MDMK chief Vaiko and eight others was binding on the Tamil Nadu government.
